/></div><div class="b160a">AP Photo/Jacquelyn Martin</div></div></figure><div class="_9aceb"><div class="_5c38a _90ad0">THE ROSTER</div><h1 class="c56f9 a1446">Company boards must navigate a minefield of influencers</h1><div class="f285a _44f1f"><div class="d04c4"><div class="_06fc1 _44f1f"><div class="ec4c3"><a class="" href="/author/john-engen/"><div><div class="_7c993"><img src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/John-Engen-e1552691922307.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=40&amp;h=40&amp;crop=1" srcSet="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/John-Engen-e1552691922307.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=40&amp;h=40&amp;crop=1 1x, https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/John-Engen-e1552691922307.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=80&amp;h=80&amp;crop=1 2x, https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/John-Engen-e1552691922307.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=120&amp;h=120&amp;crop=1 3x" sizes="" alt="John Engen" class="_955e3" decoding="async"/></div></div></a></div></div><div class="_84643 _44f1f"><span>Member exclusive by </span><a class="" href="/author/john-engen/">John Engen</a><span> for <a class="" href="/guide/the-board-is-broken/">The board is broken</a></span></div></div></div></div></header><div class="_52353 f897b"><style type="text/css">:root{--color-accent:#168dd9;--color-background-1:#f9f9f9;--color-background-1-transparent:rgba(249,249,249,0.0001);--color-background-2:#ffffff;--color-background-3:rgba(0,0,0,0.15);--color-background-4:#ffffff;--color-background-modal:rgba(249,249,249,0.98);--color-border-decorative:rgba(0,0,0,0.15);--color-border-interactive:rgba(0,0,0,0.3);--color-typography:#000000;--color-typography-faint:rgba(0,0,0,0.7);--color-ui:#000000;}@media print{:root{--color-accent:#000;--color-background-1:transparent;--color-background-1-transparent:transparent;--color-background-2:transparent;--color-background-3:transparent;--color-background-4:transparent;--color-background-5:transparent;--color-background-navigation:transparent;--color-border-decorative:#000;--color-border-interactive:#000;--color-typography:#000;--color-typography-faint:#000;--color-ui:#000;}}</style><div class="_2fd7b e1530 f897b"><div class="_8dfb8"><div id="article-content"><p class="_6bdca">Modern boards are under a lot of pressure. They must represent shareholders, work with management, and perform all sorts of compliance duties. All of their various stakeholders have demands and desires, and their goals often conflict, making the job in some ways a no-win. Here are some of the key areas and players that put pressure on boards.</p><h2 class="a539f">Activist investors</h2><p class="_6bdca">The glamor boys of the investing world, <a href="https://corpgov.law.harvard.edu/2019/01/25/dealing-with-activist-hedge-funds-and-other-activist-investors-2/">activist hedge funds</a> are renowned for taking small stakes in underperforming companies and then pressuring their boards to sell or change strategies in a way that will pump up the stock price (at least in the short term), at which point they sell for a tidy profit.</p></div></div><aside class="b9504 bc0c5"><div class="cb922"></div></aside></div><div class="b3f9f"><h2 class="c332d">You are reading a Quartz <a class="" href="/become-a-member/">member exclusive</a>.</h2><p class="_0517f"><a class="" href="/become-a-member/">Become a member</a> to keep reading this story and unlock unlimited access to all of Quartz.</p><div class="f4a11"><div class="fdf25"><div class="_6a004"><a class="_8b0be _29ebd _69a8e" href="/subscribe/">Start free trial</a></div><div class="a9f5c"><a class="eb8d5 _29ebd _69a8e" href="/login/">Log in</a></div></div></div><p class="_6b106">Membership will also get you:</p><div class="_1f0d7"><details class="_211ca fee50"><summary class="de89a"><div class="_93d86"><h3 class="_5a7de">The rest of our guide to <span class="_6c799">The board is broken</span></h3><svg class="ccf2c" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="12" height="12" 